article.headline: Liberty 88, Coker 66
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. -- Seth Curry scored 22 points to help lead Liberty to an 88-66 win over Coker on Friday night. Curry also had a game-high eight rebounds and hit four 3-pointers for the Flames (3-1), who shot 62 percent (31 of 50) from the field in the Liberty Thanksgiving Classic. Anthony Smith scored 16 points and Jesse Sanders chipped in 15. Kyle Ohman was 3-for-4 from behind the arc, scoring 13 for the game. Josh Poston scored 13 and dished out a game-high five assists to lead the Cobras (3-3), who shot 39.3 percent (24 of 61) in the loss. Stevie Evans scored 12, was 4-for-8 on 3-pointers and tallied two steals. The Flames, who led 48-27 at halftime, hit 16 free throws compared to eight by the Cobras. Liberty outrebounded Coker 32-72.
